00:00:04.440 --> 00:00:08.340
Braised Fried Tofu Pocket with Eggs

00:00:20.320 --> 00:00:26.060
Boil dried kelp pieces and make broth.

00:00:29.580 --> 00:00:32.560
Add katsuobushi into the broth.

00:00:43.700 --> 00:00:50.880
Cut the fried tofu skin in half and blanch for 3 minutes.

00:00:58.580 --> 00:01:03.280
Press it with a spoon to remove any excess moisture to prevent it from tearing.

00:01:18.200 --> 00:01:25.120
Cut and trim the carrot and radish into cylinder shape.

00:01:44.380 --> 00:01:49.240
Add in one egg into the blanched fried tofu skin.

00:01:54.760 --> 00:02:00.900
Secure it with a tooth pick (or any small skewers will do)

00:02:12.060 --> 00:02:15.120
Add some katsuobushi, soy sauce, sugar, cooking alcohol and refined rice wine to the broth.

00:02:19.080 --> 00:02:21.800
Add the carrot and radish into the broth and bring it up to a boil.

00:02:25.620 --> 00:02:28.700
Add the fried tofu pocket into the broth very carefully so that the egg inside doesn't come out.

00:02:35.200 --> 00:02:40.460
Let it boil and reduce the broth until one-third of it remains.

00:02:49.160 --> 00:02:51.860
Ingredients
2 pieces of fried tofu skin, 4 eggs, carrot, radish, 2 pieces of 6x6 centimeter dried kelp and a handful of katsuobushi

00:02:51.860 --> 00:02:54.880
Broth
1.5 cup of katsuobushi, 2T of soy sauce and 1T of sugar, cooking alcohol and refined rice wine each.

